{
  "name": "Mental Clarity",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "systems/n5eb/assets/Icons%20%26%20Images/Clans/Yamanaka.png",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>The Yamanaka are adept at mind control, suggestion, alteration, and affliction, making them far more suited to resist such attempts. </p><p>Starting at 7th level, you gain a 1d4 bonus to all saving throws against Genjutsu with the Unaware keyword, and advantage on Insight checks against creatures attempting to lie to you. </p><p>Beginning at 11th level as a bonus action, you can target one creature you can see within 60 feet and make a Wisdom or Charisma (Insight) check vs a DC (8 + their level) to learn either the targets Wisdom or Charisma score. <br />You can do this a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus per long rest</p>",
